---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Asko Dryer Repair | Southern California | Heat-Pump + Vented Condenser Swedish";
const description = "$89 dx waived. Asko dryer repair SoCal, T-series heat-pump condenser + vented, Pro-grade, stainless drum. Vara Sweden + Gorenje/Hisense parent.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/asko-dryer-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Asko dryer, heat-pump vs condenser vs vented, which is which?",
    a: "Asko ships three dryer architectures in the US, and the service approach differs for each. <b>T-series heat-pump dryer</b> (T208H and variants), closed-loop refrigerant system reheats + recycles air, no external vent needed, energy-efficient. Service considerations: refrigerant circuit is sealed (we don't service that internally; heat-pump compressor failure = major component swap $680-$980). <b>Condenser dryer</b> (T-series non-heat-pump), collects moisture in a reservoir, no vent needed; reservoir-level sensor + condenser coil cleaning are the main service items. <b>Vented dryer</b> (fewer Asko models; uncommon in US), conventional exhaust out of building, standard service approach. Most LA installs are heat-pump or condenser because the Asko customer profile has the kitchen footprint prioritized over venting runs."
  },
  {
    q: "What's different about heat-pump dryer service vs conventional vented?",
    a: "Four meaningful differences: (1) <b>No external vent</b>, so the \"dryer takes forever\" call isn't lint-clogged duct, it's usually evaporator-coil debris buildup (lint gets past the filter into the heat-pump evaporator) or refrigerant-side problem. Evaporator cleaning service $140-$220. (2) <b>Lower drying temperature</b> (typically 120-140°F vs 160-180°F on vented), clothes dry slower but gentler. (3) <b>Reservoir or condensate drain</b>, if the reservoir isn't emptying or drain is blocked, the dryer halts cycle. Reservoir-level sensor $100-$160 or drain-line clearing ($89 diagnostic-only often resolves). (4) <b>Heat-pump compressor</b> is a sealed system, failure is rare but expensive ($680-$980 including install + refrigerant recovery)."
  },
  {
    q: "Asko dryer + Asko washer stacked, any service consideration?",
    a: "Asko washer + dryer stack is common in LA condos and Westside luxury laundry rooms. <b>Structural consideration</b>: the stacking kit (Asko-specific hardware) needs to be verified as properly installed, an incorrectly bracketed stack means the dryer walks during spin cycles on the washer below. <b>Vibration interaction</b>: if the washer has a shock-absorber issue, the dryer on top amplifies the movement; we check both units during diagnostic when a stacked install shows vibration. <b>Shared electrical</b>: stacked installs typically run one 240V circuit, if the breaker is tripping, both units' power consumption together is often the root cause rather than either unit individually. We look at the whole stack during service calls."
  },
  {
    q: "Stainless drum on a dryer, does this matter?",
    a: "Yes, but differently than on the washer. On the washer side, stainless drum matters because of wet + detergent corrosion exposure. On the dryer side, stainless drum matters because of <b>heat exposure</b>, plastic drum interiors (some low-end US dryers) can develop heat-warping after 8-10 years of high-temperature cycles, causing uneven drying. Asko dryers use stainless drum throughout the lineup, which avoids that failure mode entirely. Practical impact: Asko dryers don't have the \"replace the drum liner\" service category that occasionally surfaces on mass-market dryers. The drum itself runs the lifetime of the unit."
  },
  {
    q: "Asko US parts chain for dryers, service expectations?",
    a: "Same as Asko washer, the US parts network is thinner than Whirlpool-family or Electrolux-family brands. Common dryer service items (door switches, thermistors, drum belts on vented variants, lint-filter sensors, control-board mainstream SKUs) have adequate US distributor stock; 3-7 day delivery to LA. Specialty heat-pump compressor parts and Asko-specific programming boards can run 2-4 week Sweden factory lead. We set realistic expectations during diagnostic. Gorenje + Hisense cross-references sometimes shorten wait on motors + heating elements (shared corporate parts catalog), but brand-specific control + trim stays Asko-exclusive."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Asko dryer repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic $89 waived with repair. Typical Asko dryer bands: evaporator coil cleaning (heat-pump) $140–$220; condenser coil cleaning $140–$220; reservoir-level sensor $100–$160; thermistor $80–$140; door switch / latch $100–$180; lint-filter sensor $80–$140; drum belt (vented models) $80–$140; main control board $320–$520; heating element (vented models) $180–$280; heat-pump compressor $680–$980 (rare; major repair, refrigerant-sealed system). Swedish specialty parts 2-4 week factory lead on non-stock items."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Asko Dryer Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$"
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Asko Dryer Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Asko dryer repair across Southern California, LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. T-series heat-pump condenser (no vent required, sealed-refrigerant) + condenser reservoir + vented variants. Stainless drum throughout lineup. Vara Sweden factory; Gorenje/Hisense parent. Pairs with matching Asko washer for stacked installs. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Asko", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/asko/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Asko Dryer Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Asko dryer service?</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Asko › Dryer Repair</div>
    <h1>Asko Dryer Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Asko's dryer line is built for vent-less installation, T-series heat-pump dryers recycle air through a sealed refrigerant loop (no external vent required, energy-efficient), T-series condenser dryers collect moisture in a reservoir, and a smaller set of vented models for installs that can run exhaust duct. All use stainless drums throughout (no plastic-liner heat-warping at 8-10 years). LA customers spec Asko dryers most in condos + Westside luxury laundry rooms where venting a conventional dryer would require structural changes, the heat-pump variant removes that constraint entirely. Vara Sweden factory; Gorenje/Hisense parent preserves Swedish engineering identity. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Heat-pump + condenser + vented</b>, three architectures, vent-less options</li>
      <li><b>Stainless drum throughout</b>, avoids heat-warping failure mode</li>
      <li><b>Vara Sweden factory</b>, Gorenje/Hisense parent; specialty parts 2-4 week</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What Asko dryer repair typically costs</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Evaporator coil cleaning (heat-pump)</td><td>$140 – $220</td><td>Most common "takes forever" call</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Condenser coil cleaning</td><td>$140 – $220</td><td>Condenser-variant dryers</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Reservoir-level sensor</td><td>$100 – $160</td><td>Halts cycle when "full" false-trigger</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermistor</td><td>$80 – $140</td><td>Temperature sensing drift</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Door switch / latch</td><td>$100 – $180</td><td>Common safety interlock</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drum belt (vented models)</td><td>$80 – $140</td><td>Non-heat-pump only</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Main control board</td><td>$320 – $520</td><td>Sweden factory lead on specialty</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Heating element (vented)</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Conventional resistive</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Heat-pump compressor</td><td>$680 – $980</td><td>Rare; refrigerant-sealed major</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/asko-dishwasher-repair/">Asko brand hub</a> · <a href="/brands/asko-washer-repair/">Asko washer (stacked-suite peer)</a> · <a href="/brands/asko-dishwasher-repair/">Asko dishwasher</a> · <a href="/brands/miele-dryer-repair/">Miele dryer (European premium peer)</a> · <a href="/services/dryer-repair/">Dryer repair (service hub)</a> · <a href="/price-list/dryer-repair-cost/">Dryer repair cost</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Heat-pump dryer in LA, why the architecture matters</h2>
    <p>The single biggest reason LA customers choose Asko dryers is <b>vent-less heat-pump capability</b>. Traditional vented dryers need an exhaust duct through an exterior wall or roof, which is a major constraint in condo laundry closets, Westside historic homes, and renovations where running new duct isn't practical. Asko heat-pump dryers use a sealed refrigerant loop to recycle air: no duct, no venting, installable almost anywhere with a 240V outlet and a floor drain or reservoir.</p>
    <p>Service implications: lint gets past the filter into the evaporator coil over time (typical 2-3 year service interval), so "dryer isn't drying properly" on a heat-pump Asko is usually evaporator cleaning ($140-$220, often no parts) rather than heating-element replacement. The refrigerant circuit is sealed and we don't service that internally; compressor failure is rare ($680-$980 major repair when it happens). Overall, Asko heat-pump dryers need different diagnostic thinking than conventional vented dryers, but the install-anywhere flexibility makes them the correct answer for a growing share of LA laundry rooms.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Asko dryer repair, frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Asko dryer service? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair across Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .small { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-top: 12px; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
